==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|frm|inflammable}}, from {{der|en|ML.|īnflammābilis}}, from {{der|en|la|inflammo|īnflammāre|t=to set on fire}}, from {{m|la|in|t=in, on}} + {{m|la|flamma|t=flame}}.  Equivalent to {{suffix|en|inflame|able}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ĭnʹflăm-ə-bəl}}, {{IPA|en|/ɪnˈflæməbəl/}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-inflammable.wav|Audio (Southern England)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Capable of burning; easily set on [[fire]].
#: {{syn|en|combustible|flammable}}
#: {{ant|en|fireproof|incombustible|nonflammable|noninflammable|unflammable|uninflammable}}
#* {{RQ:Haggard She|passage=On he went a few paces and touched a second, then a third, and a fourth, till at last we were surrounded on all three sides by a great ring of bodies flaring furiously, the material with which they were preserved having rendered them so '''inflammable''' that the flames would literally spout out of the ears and mouth in tongues of fire a foot or more in length.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Easily excited; [[set off]] by the slightest excuse; easily [[enrage]]d or [[inflame]]d.
#: {{syn|en|hot-headed|[[quick]] to [[anger]]}}
#: {{ant|en|level-headed|unflappable}}
# {{lb|en|nonstandard}} Incapable of burning; not easily set on [[fire]].
#: {{syn|en|fireproof|incombustible|nonflammable|noninflammable|unflammable|uninflammable}}
#: {{ant|en|combustible|flammable}}

====Usage notes====
* {{m|en||Inflammable}}, although used for centuries [[synonymous]]ly with the more recent back-formation {{m|en|flammable}}, nowadays also has significant [[nonstandard]] use as an [[antonym]] of {{m|en|flammable}}, and as such, may be taken to have the opposite meaning to that intended (depending on whether the writer and/or the reader use {{m|en||inflammable}} as a synonym, or as an antonym, of {{m|en|flammable}}). Where such confusion might arise, especially where this may be a safety hazard, one may prefer to use {{m|en|flammable}} or {{m|en|non-flammable}} (depending on whether {{m|en||inflammable}} would have been used as a [[synonym]] or as an [[antonym]] of {{m|en|flammable}}) or another [[synonym]].

